===Noun phrase===
{{en-noun|sg=[[lowest]] [[common]] [[denominator]]}}

# (''Mathematics'') The smallest shared [[multiple]] of the denominators of several [[fractions]].
#:''The '''lowest common denominator''' of one-half and one-quarter is four.''
# The simplest or basest shared interest or characteristic among a group or collection of people etc.
#:''Reality TV really is appealing to the '''lowest common denominator''' in audiences.''

